description: This is a fairly flat trail network that loops around the snowmobile trails. Forest varies from deciduous to cultivated pine trees. Great short hike to take your dog for a walk.The area can be quite muddy in the spring time.
directions: From Newmarket: follow Yonge st into Holland Landing. Take a right onto Cedar St. Trail head is on the north side of the street at the end of the cul-de-sac.See google map on this page or download the GPS information.
title: Holland Landing Prairie Nature Reserve
